subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia (
Fig. 13E–G
):

Epandrium relatively long and convex. Hypandrial arms long, not or slightly bent anteriorly. Basal 1/2 of cerci prominent in lateral view, distal 1/2 massive and strongly bent posteriorly (
Fig. 13E
). Posterior surface of distal 1/2 of cerci flat (
Fig. 13F, G
). Medial preapical tooth of cerci not developed. Distal 1/2 of surstylus, in lateral view, narrow and evenly curved posteriorly, slightly pointed apically (
Fig. 13E
); posterior surface of surstylus grooved (concave) (
Fig. 13E–G
). Basal 1/2 of surstylus wide.
